From c2cfcd55e239afe660802e66b6a27dedfce38f96 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 20:14:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix schema drift, broken tests, and pipeline safety bugs

- routes.py: fix NameError in GET /api/model-status (referenced removed
  AgentRoute class; now uses AgentRouteFallback, the actual current model).

- test_schema.py / conftest.py: update stale tests/fixtures left over from
  the AgentRoute -> AgentRouteFallback / ProviderKey schema migration.
  Previously `pytest tests/` aborted collection entirely with an
  ImportError, so the documented test command produced zero results.

- browser.py: make the cloakbrowser launch lazy (on first get_page() call)
  instead of eager at app startup. Previously every API request required
  a browser binary download, which blocked the entire test_routes.py
  suite (86 tests) in any environment without open network access to
  cloakbrowser's CDN/GitHub releases.

- conftest.py: stop the `client` fixture from re-seeding ~150 default
  worlds via init_db() on every test (masked until the browser fix above
  unblocked test_routes.py; several "empty DB" assertions were failing
  against a database quietly pre-populated with seed data).

- nodes.py:
  * architecture_node's stability check no longer relies on a
    case-sensitive "STATUS: STABLE" substring match plus a near-dead
    "ANOMALY not in text" fallback (which was almost always false since
    the required output format always includes an ANOMALY_DETAILS
    label). Now explicitly parses the STATUS field.
  * added a bounded retry cap (MAX_ARCHITECTURE_ATTEMPTS=5) to the
    architecture<->critic audit loop, which previously had no limit and
    could retry indefinitely.
  * architecture_node now reuses the tested audit_success() helper
    instead of a separate, less strict inline check.
  * tier-extraction regex failures are now logged instead of silently
    defaulting to Tier 11 with no trace.
  * research_node now short-circuits to FINISHED (with a FAILED log
    entry) when every world in a batch fails research, instead of
    continuing to burn LLM calls in consolidation/architecture on an
    empty dataset.

- state.py / routes.py: add architecture_attempts counter to pipeline
  state, initialized in the orchestration input payload.

- router.py: provider_id is now an explicit, consumed parameter used to
  filter the fallback chain, instead of silently leaking into **kwargs
  and getting forwarded straight into litellm.acompletion(). Also
  removed a duplicate `router = ModelRouter()` instantiation.

- web_fetch.py: reject non-http(s) URL schemes before fetching, closing
  off an obvious SSRF vector for the research agent's fetchPage tool.

- test.sh: fall back to venv/ (not just .venv/) like run.sh already
  does, so the documented `./setup.sh && ./test.sh` flow doesn't
  silently fall through to system Python and fail with "No module
  named pytest".

Verified: `./test.sh` now runs end-to-end offline -- 191/191 fast
backend tests pass, slow (network/LLM-gated) tests fail soft as
designed, and all 7 frontend tests pass.
